# Relaxed RTKProcessor Internal Gates

Apply to third_party/gnssplusplus/src/algorithms/rtk.cpp on top of the
`apps/gnss_solve.cpp` outer-guard patch (see
`libgnssplusplus_relaxed_guards.patch`).

## Changes

### 1. `processRTKEpoch` trusted-jump cap (line ~1216)

```diff
                 const double trusted_jump =
                     (solution.position_ecef - saved_last_trusted_position).norm();
-                const double max_trusted_jump = std::max(8.0, 12.0 * dt);
+                const double max_trusted_jump = std::max(50.0, 60.0 * dt);
                 if (trusted_jump > max_trusted_jump) {
```

### 2. `updateFilter` measurement thresholds (line ~1624)

```diff
 bool RTKProcessor::updateFilter(const std::map<SatelliteId, SatelliteData>& sat_data) {
     if (sat_data.size() < 4) return false;

     auto measurement_system = rtk_measurement::assembleMeasurementSystem(
         buildMeasurementBlocks(sat_data), filter_state_.state.size());
     const auto update_result = rtk_update::applyMeasurementUpdate(filter_state_.state,
                                                                   filter_state_.covariance,
                                                                   measurement_system,
-                                                                  30.0,
-                                                                  6);
+                                                                  60.0,
+                                                                  4);
     return update_result.ok;
 }
```

## Effect on PPC2024 honest aggregate

| Stage | Aggregate |
|---|---:|
| Session start (signoff) | 33.65% |
| Patch 1 (outer guards) | 46.14% |
| **+ Patch 2 (inner gates)** | **47.84%** |
| TURING target | 85.60% |

+1.70 pp over outer guards alone. nagoya/run1 gains the most (+9.70 pp),
tokyo/run1 +4.36 pp. Some segments regress slightly.

## Follow-ups

- Expose the three thresholds as CLI flags (`--max-trusted-jump-m`,
  `--filter-outlier-threshold`, `--filter-min-observations`).
- Lower `rtk_config_.min_lock_count` default from its current value.
- Add IMU predict stage in `processRTKEpoch` before the KF update so the
  filter survives extended signal blackouts.
- Evaluate raising the `kReacquireFixedCount` (currently 5) so that hold
  ambiguity does not drop as quickly.
